<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EBAFF3448A7528DFE2BF87D" pageId="244" pageNumber="245" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EBAFF3448A7528DFD4AF899" blockId="244.[151,1438,1441,2005]" pageId="244" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EBAFF3448A7528DFE0FFA49" bold="true" box="[151,426,1441,1466]" pageId="244" pageNumber="245">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EBAFF344A81528DFCA9FA49" box="[689,780,1441,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.4" pageId="244" pageNumber="245" unit="mm" value="9.4">9.4 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible, clypeus, gena and anterior region of face near clypeus testaceous; antenna testaceous, except segments 3–10 darkened; mesosoma black, except posterior and lateral regions of pronotum reddish; metasoma testaceous; legs testaceous, except clubs of pro- and metafemur brown. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 27:9:55:70:71:78:50:20:14:16. Head dull, reticulate rugose; frontal line hardly visible; occipital carina incomplete, laterally not reaching eyes; POL = 6; OL = 2.5; OOL = 18; OPL = 5; TL = 4. Pronotum dull, rugose, crossed by transverse impression, sculptured by many transverse keels. Scutum dull, rugose, with numerous irregular keels. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.6 length of scutum. Scutellum and metanotum dull, smooth, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Propodeum reticulate rugose, without transverse or longitudinal keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein longer than proximal part (50:32). Protarsal segments in following proportions: 59:8:16:53:76. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EBAFF344C305025FBD4F8D1" box="[1024,1137,1801,1825]" captionStart="PLATE 70" captionStartId="243.[151,233,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[186,1424,183,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-72@243.[151,1436,161,1926]" captionTargetPageId="243" captionText="PLATE 70. A. Tuft of long hairs on antennal segment. B–D. Chelae, holotypes. A. Thaumatodryinus sp., female (from Olmi 1984). B. Th. alienus (from Olmi 1987a). C. T. asiaticus (from Olmi 1984). D. T. beckeri (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.21 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and 0.44 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278621/files/figure.png" pageId="244" pageNumber="245">Plate 70D</figureCitation>
) with two subapical teeth and one row of about 40 lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EBAFF344B195001FC32F8B5" box="[809,919,1837,1861]" captionStart="PLATE 70" captionStartId="243.[151,233,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[186,1424,183,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-72@243.[151,1436,161,1926]" captionTargetPageId="243" captionText="PLATE 70. A. Tuft of long hairs on antennal segment. B–D. Chelae, holotypes. A. Thaumatodryinus sp., female (from Olmi 1984). B. Th. alienus (from Olmi 1987a). C. T. asiaticus (from Olmi 1984). D. T. beckeri (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.21 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and 0.44 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278621/files/figure.png" pageId="244" pageNumber="245">Plate 70D</figureCitation>
) with two rows of approximately 65 lamellae; distal apex with about 15 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EBAFF3448F75059FE2BF87D" blockId="244.[151,1438,1441,2005]" box="[199,398,1909,1933]" pageId="244" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EBAFF3448F75059FEAEF87D" bold="true" box="[199,267,1909,1933]" pageId="244" pageNumber="245">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
